A. Offline Processing Terms

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of the Software, to deal in the Software without restriction apart from live streaming as defined above which is prohibited, including without limitation the rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is furnished to do so, subject to the inclusion of this license notice in all copies or substantial portions of the Software.

B. Real-time Processing Terms

1. Standard License Limitations. Organization may use the Software for real-time processing only if it meets ALL of the following criteria: a) Organization employs fifty (50) or fewer individuals globally across all affiliates and/or subsidiaries; b) Organization maintains fewer than ten thousand (10,000) peak concurrent viewers in any rolling 30-day period; c) Organization deploys the Software on no more than fifty (50) physical or virtual machines simultaneously

2. Trial Period License. New Organizations may utilize the Software for commercial purposes for a 90-day trial period, regardless of organization size or usage volume. To continue using the Software, at the end of the Trial Period Organizations must either: a) Comply with Standard License Limitations, or b) Obtain a Commercial License. New Organization shall mean an Organization that has not used the Software at any time in the past. Standard License Limitations shall not apply to the Trial Period.

3. Prohibited Uses. The following uses are expressly prohibited without a Commercial License: a) Offering or operating any Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) solution that provides programmatic video control capabilities utilizing the Software; b) Incorporating, embedding, integrating, or bundling the Software into any software application or hardware product intended for distribution or sale

4. Commercial License. Organizations exceeding any limitations in Standard License Limitations or requiring prohibited uses must obtain a Commercial License. Commercial licensing starts at $1,000 per month. Contact [contact@smelter.dev](mailto:contact@smelter.dev) for terms.

